  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to investigate the reliability of the Melbourne Assessment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Children with central motor disorders will be tested twice within one week with the Melbourne
      Assessment. The assessments will be video scored. At a later time point, different raters
      will rate the same video for inter-rater reliability, the same rater will score the same
      video for intra-rater reliability, and the same rater will score the repeated assessment
      videos for test-retest reliability.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
